replies.body:
Hi TurtleSaurusRex! 
Thanks for the report! I've got some good news for ya, it looks like we have a fix going into the 8.8 patch, which should be hitting live next week. If something still seems off in the new patch, please let me know! 

{{sticker:sg-ahri-2}}

My intent wasn't to discount any personal issues you have when playing the skins, but I did want to give full visibility on why the skin was developed the way it was. One of the biggest discussion points was surrounding his run animation and why the team didn't veer in the direction of something totally new.

Additionally, I did want to ask for more context around what you're describing because these skins use the same run animations, but after loading them up in game, it appears there's a small difference -  the arms and how they're swinging. Base Blitzcrank's arms are looser and swing more freely, as opposed to the skins where they sway closer to his body because of the skin's model design. So, the *run* itself is the same, but the arms swing a bit differently because of the design of the skin, particularly the drill arm.

I'm more than happy to raise your concerns to the team, and it's something we can keep in mind for skins in the future. I'm not sure we'd be able to make the Lancer skins' arms swing like base Blitzcrank's, though, because of the drill that he has on his right arm; the model and rig isn't built to swing much more freely like base. ;-;
